the independence of the Court.]

381
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:54,130
Judges who give sentences
that don't meet the new guidelines

382
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:57,170
and dismiss a large number of warrants
will be subject to disciplinary action?

383
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:59,870
The Blue House wants
to strengthen order and discipline.

384
00:27:59,940 --> 00:28:01,610
Shouldn't the Court cooperate?

385
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:04,510
Does the Court exist just to cooperate
with the Blue House?

386
00:28:04,580 --> 00:28:06,010
Without a nation,

387
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:09,650
there is no independence of the Court.

388
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:11,480
For this nation to exist,

389
00:28:12,090 --> 00:28:15,420
the Court's independence
should be guaranteed, sir.

390
00:28:24,330 --> 00:28:26,370
[Was the foundation chair title
not enough for you?]

391
00:28:26,970 --> 00:28:27,970
This is funny.

392
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:31,910
You think you have the means
to support me?

393
00:28:33,370 --> 00:28:36,180
You're hurting my feelings here.
I'm being sincere.

394
00:28:38,380 --> 00:28:39,380
Sincere?

395
00:28:39,750 --> 00:28:42,920
Yes, I'm forever indebted to you.

396
00:28:42,980 --> 00:28:44,750
Because I shook up your sheep farm

397
00:28:44,820 --> 00:28:47,190
and helped you steal the position?

398
00:28:47,690 --> 00:28:48,690
Is that it?

399
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:51,520
Yes, I'm grateful for that too.

400
00:28:51,590 --> 00:28:53,130
But it's much more than that.

401
00:28:53,990 --> 00:28:56,060
It was at your house

402
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:59,470
that I saw how beautiful this world can be
for the first time in my life.

403
00:28:59,530 --> 00:29:02,140
Everything there sparkled and dazzled.

404
00:29:02,270 --> 00:29:04,670
I lived so I could go back there.

405
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:07,540
As the owner, not as a petty thief.

406
00:29:09,410 --> 00:29:11,780
To become the owner of the world

407
00:29:12,250 --> 00:29:13,510
you chased me out from.

408
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:15,480
You haven't changed.

409
00:29:16,250 --> 00:29:18,020
You are still no more than

410
00:29:18,350 --> 00:29:20,320
a hungry, petty thief.

411
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:23,760
You don't even know
how low you had to stoop.

412
00:29:24,020 --> 00:29:25,290
A petty thief.

413
00:29:31,730 --> 00:29:32,870
You know,

414
00:29:35,170 --> 00:29:37,770
I like you when you get like this.

415
00:29:39,170 --> 00:29:41,980
When you ridicule me, curse me out,

416
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:43,580
and hurt my feelings.

417
00:29:44,410 --> 00:29:45,580
It's a thrill.

418
00:29:46,480 --> 00:29:47,810
So you make me want

419
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:50,380
to torture you too.

420
00:29:51,680 --> 00:29:55,050
I want to scratch you, bite you,

421
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:56,590
and dig my nails into you.

422
00:30:01,330 --> 00:30:03,030
You still don't know anything about me.

423
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:05,870
I'm not patient.

424
00:30:12,570 --> 00:30:14,440
I don't discriminate against people
based on gender.

425
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:20,780
I...

426
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:29,660
treat them exactly the same.

427
00:30:33,830 --> 00:30:36,330
You and I are very similar.

428
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:40,100
Is that why you like me?

429
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:42,470
Yes.

430
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:45,510
How much do you like me?

431
00:30:50,780 --> 00:30:52,380
How much do you like me?

432
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:11,130
What are you doing?

433
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:15,300
Are you all right?

434
00:31:16,600 --> 00:31:17,700
I'm okay.

435
00:31:17,870 --> 00:31:19,270
You saved my life.

436
00:31:20,810 --> 00:31:22,040
Okay.

437
00:31:25,810 --> 00:31:27,250
Mr. Kang. What on earth...

438
00:31:29,220 --> 00:31:30,480
I'll get going today.

439
00:31:31,180 --> 00:31:32,250
See you around.

440
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:47,930
Darn it.

441
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:51,670
She's in charge of running a task force
to support our department.

442
00:31:52,370 --> 00:31:53,510
Ms. Jung is?

443
00:31:57,480 --> 00:31:59,180
Hello, Ms. Jung.

444
00:31:59,250 --> 00:32:02,680
Ms. Oh. You still owe me
a private conversation with you.

445
00:32:08,290 --> 00:32:10,190
What was that? Come on.

446
00:32:18,700 --> 00:32:19,730
Mr. Kang.

447
00:32:20,870 --> 00:32:22,670
Am I part of this department?

448
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,070
What do you mean?

449
00:32:24,140 --> 00:32:26,570
The whole country is stirred up
because of what you started.

450
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:28,540
But you still have not told me a thing.

451
00:32:28,610 --> 00:32:30,680
You said you would resign
without talking to us.

452
00:32:30,740 --> 00:32:32,650
But now, you're asking
the public for tip-offs.

453
00:32:33,110 --> 00:32:35,350
And why is that woman doing here
all of a sudden?

454
00:32:35,820 --> 00:32:37,250
-Ms. Oh.
-Wait.

455
00:32:37,420 --> 00:32:38,690
I have one more thing to say.

456
00:32:41,820 --> 00:32:44,890
I don't know how you think of me.

457
00:32:44,990 --> 00:32:46,830
But I am still a judge.

458
00:32:46,890 --> 00:32:48,600
And I'm a member of this department.

459
00:32:48,660 --> 00:32:50,530
Unless you treat me like one,
you're on your own.

460
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,570
You've changed.

461
00:32:53,530 --> 00:32:55,970
"If you just let me join
the Live Court Department"

462
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:59,410
"and sit next to you, it will be
an honor for the rest of my life."

463
00:32:59,740 --> 00:33:00,810
Isn't that what you said?

464
00:33:00,870 --> 00:33:02,280
I remember you telling me that.

465
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:04,040
You sound ambitious now.

466
00:33:05,010 --> 00:33:08,410
I should congratulate you,
but I wonder what caused this change.

467
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:11,520
I told you everything I have to say.

468
00:33:24,860 --> 00:33:26,530
Is this your way of handling things?

469
00:33:26,730 --> 00:33:29,000
You're pushing away people
who are on your side.

470
00:33:29,070 --> 00:33:31,540
How can you go up against
these world leaders?

471
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:32,970
You have no one.

472
00:33:35,510 --> 00:33:36,740
Let's talk about that later.

473
00:33:39,210 --> 00:33:40,350
Stop by my house.

474
00:33:41,310 --> 00:33:43,620
Elijah seems anxious and concerned.

475
00:33:47,350 --> 00:33:50,660
